my sweet love

Going to try and keep this as short as possible lol. At the beginning of this year sooo many things in my life had changed and I remember feeling so confused & frustrated, but still very optimistic of what could happen. All those feelings inspired me to write F*ck Daises as a letter to self & a reminder to recognize things for what they are and to continue choosing myself. One of the most memorable moments I had during that time was the immense amount
of support and love from my friends and my family, ESPECIALLY my mom. My mom called me everyday to speak love into my spirit (as she’s done my entire life) & when I didn’t answer she never missed an opportunity to leave me a message. After all that anger and confusion, so much beauty entered my life and even more changed. I headlined my first show, went on my first tour, traveled the world, released beautiful music, & fell in love with so many new things. I don’t even recognize who I was at the beginning of this year anymore. Change can feel like the worse thing in the world sometimes, but it’s so necessary for growth & transformation.

With that being saidddd, tomorrow I want to bring you guys into what that process was like for me. F*ck Daises Visualizer tomorrow at 12pm 🤍

F*CK DAISES (VISUALIZER) IS OUTTTT ✨🤍

I’m so happy to finally share this w y’all. The process of creating all of this is very special and sentimental for me. I hope you guys enjoy 🤍

biggest of thank you’s to my amazing team @naj_mullah & @daijahanasa and the phenomenal crew I had the blessing of collabing with & who made it all possible 🤍

bts from shoot day of ‘F*ck Daises’ visualizer. this was such a smooth day. we were so ahead of schedule which gave us more time to talk & get to know each other. We whipped out the spades & everything 😂 I remember being so tired bc I had a show the night before & only got like 3 hours of sleep 😭 so i had to sneak in some naps. but I would do it all again and wouldn’t change a thing. 

thank you @moments_in_between___ & @officialdataheist for making the experience so beautiful and seamless 🤍

with this visual I wanted to show the challenges of working, pursuing a creative career, & dealing w love and heartbreak all at once. sometimes it can feel so heavy and discouraging, but there’s so much beauty that comes with it all when you embrace the journey and allow yourself to experience & grow! thank you for all the love so far on the song and visual 🤍 if you haven’t seen it yet click that link babe! 😇

Our next guest on Dead or Alive is singer/songwriter Payton Moore! In this episode we talk about her single “fuck daisies” and making it with friends, going on tour with Ambre earlier this year, the 3 people that she would meet Dead or Alive, and more. It was such a joy to sit down and get to learn more about her artistry and the journey to where she is now!

2023 has been the most amazing year i’ve had so far. i’m so grateful and so deeply appreciative of everyone who’s been a part of it and everyone who’s supported me. 

i headlined my 1st show in my hometown
went on my first tour!?!?
released some of my personal favorite songs i’ve created
traveled all year long & went to countries i’ve always dreamed of going
soo many shows, so many new faces, new friends.
I shed a lotttt of skin this year and focused on what actually aligned with me and followed my intuition through and through.

THANK YOU 2023 💛 i’m so excited for what next year brings me 🥰
